00:27:38,073 --> 00:27:40,575
I don't believe this. I
don't believe the top brass...

465
00:27:40,743 --> 00:27:43,911
...of a national television network
are sitting around their salads...

466
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:46,831
The top brass of a bankrupt
national television network...

467
00:27:46,999 --> 00:27:49,250
...with projected losses
of close to $150 million.

468
00:27:49,418 --> 00:27:50,668
I don't care how bankrupt.

469
00:27:52,171 --> 00:27:56,049
You can't be seriously proposing, and
the rest of us seriously considering...

470
00:27:56,216 --> 00:27:59,093
...putting on a pornographic
Network News show.

471
00:27:59,261 --> 00:28:01,012
- The FCC'd kill us.
- Sit down, Nelson.

472
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:03,931
The FCC can't do anything
except rap our knuckles.

473
00:28:04,099 --> 00:28:07,185
I don't even wanna think about
the litigious possibilities, Frank.

474
00:28:07,353 --> 00:28:10,605
- Could be up to our ears in lawsuits.
- The affiliates won't carry it.

475
00:28:10,773 --> 00:28:13,691
Affiliates will kiss your ass,
if you can hand them a hit show.

476
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:14,901
The popular reaction...

477
00:28:15,069 --> 00:28:18,112
We don't know the popular
reaction. We have to find out.

478
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:19,322
The New York Times...

479
00:28:19,490 --> 00:28:22,825
The New York Times doesn't
advertise on our network.

480
00:28:24,953 --> 00:28:29,082
All I know is this violates every
canon of respectable broadcasting.

481
00:28:29,625 --> 00:28:32,377
We're not a respectable network.
We're a whorehouse network.

482
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:34,796
We have to take whatever we can get.

483
00:28:36,215 --> 00:28:37,799
Well, I don't want any part of it.

484
00:28:37,966 --> 00:28:40,551
I don't fancy myself the
president of a whorehouse.

485
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:43,429
That's very commendable of
you, Nelson. Now, sit down.

486
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:48,976
Your indignation has been duly
recorded. You can always resign tomorrow.

487
00:28:50,938 --> 00:28:54,315
Now look, what in
substance are we proposing?

488
00:28:54,858 --> 00:28:58,653
Merely to add editorial comment
to our Network News show.

489
00:28:58,821 --> 00:29:02,490
Brinkley, Sevareid, Reasoner,
all have their comments.

490
00:29:02,658 --> 00:29:04,617
Now Howard Beale will have his.

491
00:29:04,785 --> 00:29:08,329
I think we ought to give it a shot.
Let's see what happens tonight.

492
00:29:08,497 --> 00:29:09,539
Telephone, please.

493
00:29:09,706 --> 00:29:12,625
I don't wanna be the messenger
that has to tell Max Schumacher.

494
00:29:12,793 --> 00:29:14,710
Max doesn't work at
this network anymore.

495
00:29:14,878 --> 00:29:16,379
Mr. Ruddy fired him last night.

496
00:29:16,547 --> 00:29:19,257
Bob McDonough's running
the news division now.

497
00:29:20,801 --> 00:29:22,677
Bob McDonough in News, please.

498
00:29:24,263 --> 00:29:26,180
Oh, I don't know.

499
00:29:26,348 --> 00:29:28,766
I may teach or I may write a book...

500
00:29:28,934 --> 00:29:31,352
...whatever the hell one
does when one approaches...

501
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:33,896
...the autumn of one's years.

502
00:29:35,899 --> 00:29:38,151
My God, is that me?

503
00:29:38,444 --> 00:29:40,528
- Was I ever that young?
- Ha, ha.

504
00:29:41,196 --> 00:29:43,614
No. Howard just brought in
a picture of Ed Murrow...

505
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:46,117
...and the whole CBS
gang when we were there.

506
00:29:46,285 --> 00:29:47,618
You wouldn't believe it.

507
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:51,998
Walter Cronkite, Harry
Reasoner, Hollenbeck, Bob Trout.

508
00:29:52,166 --> 00:29:54,083
- Is that you,
Howard? - Mm-hm.

509
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:56,711
Yeah.

510
00:29:57,045 --> 00:29:59,881
- Okay, Dick, we'll be in touch. Right.
- You remember this kid?

511
00:30:00,048 --> 00:30:03,384
He's the kid I think you once sent out to
interview Cleveland Amory on vivisection.

512
00:30:07,181 --> 00:30:09,056
What's so funny?

513
00:30:11,977 --> 00:30:15,480
So I jump out of bed in my pajamas,
I grab my raincoat, I run downstairs.

514
00:30:15,647 --> 00:30:18,065
I run out in the
street and I hail a cab.

515
00:30:18,233 --> 00:30:20,234
And I jumped in and
I yell at the driver:

516
00:30:20,402 --> 00:30:23,321
"Take me to the middle of the
George Washington Bridge. "

517
00:30:25,449 --> 00:30:29,118
And the driver turns around and he
says: "Don't do it, buddy, don't do it.

518
00:30:29,286 --> 00:30:31,704
You're young, you got your
whole life ahead of you. "

519
00:30:31,872 --> 00:30:34,832
Ha-ha-ha! Wait a
minute! Wait a minute!

520
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,667
If you think that's funny...

521
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:39,378
No, if you think that's
funny, wait till you hear this.

522
00:30:39,546 --> 00:30:41,797
I've just come back from
Frank Hackett's office.

523
00:30:41,965 --> 00:30:43,716
He wants to put Howard on the air.

524
00:30:43,884 --> 00:30:45,301
- You're kidding.
- Apparently...

525
00:30:45,469 --> 00:30:47,678
...the ratings went up
five points last night...

526
00:30:47,846 --> 00:30:50,973
...and he wants Howard to go back
on and do his angry-man thing.

527
00:30:51,642 --> 00:30:53,142
What are you talking about?

528
00:30:53,310 --> 00:30:56,270
I'm telling you. They want Howard
to go back on and yell "bullshit. "

529
00:30:59,525 --> 00:31:02,860
They want Howard to go on
spontaneously letting out his anger.

530
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:05,905
A latter-day prophet denouncing
the hypocrisies of our times.

531
00:31:06,073 --> 00:31:08,199
Hey, that sounds pretty good.

532
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:10,535
Who's this "they"?

533
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:14,747
Hackett. Chaney was there.
The Legal Affairs guy.

534
00:31:14,915 --> 00:31:16,832
Oh, and that girl from Programming.

535
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,001
Christensen? What's
she got to do with this?

536
00:31:19,169 --> 00:31:21,671
You're kidding, aren't you?
- I'm not kidding.

537
00:31:21,838 --> 00:31:22,880
I told them. I said:

538
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:25,633
"Look, we're running a news
department, not a circus.

539
00:31:25,801 --> 00:31:28,135
And Howard Beale's not a bearded lady.

540
00:31:28,303 --> 00:31:30,972
If you think I'm gonna go along
with this bastardization...

541
00:31:31,139 --> 00:31:34,350
...you can have my resignation along
with Max Schumacher's right now.

542
00:31:34,518 --> 00:31:37,311
I think I'm speaking for Howard
Beale and everybody else... "

543
00:31:37,479 --> 00:31:40,523
That's my job you're turning down.

544
00:31:40,816 --> 00:31:43,276
I'd go nuts without some kind of work.

545
00:31:43,443 --> 00:31:47,738
What's wrong with being an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times?

546
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:49,699
What do you think, Max?

547
00:31:49,866 --> 00:31:53,452
Do you want to be an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times?

548
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:58,040
Yeah, I think I'd like to be an angry prophet
denouncing the hypocrisies of our times.

549
00:31:59,418 --> 00:32:01,294
Then grab it. Grab it!

550
00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:09,677
- Afternoon, Mr. Ruddy.
- Good afternoon.

551
00:32:09,845 --> 00:32:11,804
Good afternoon, Mr. Ruddy.

552
00:32:14,975 --> 00:32:17,768
- He's waiting for you,
Mr. Ruddy. Thank you.

553
00:32:23,567 --> 00:32:27,862
Nelson Chaney tells me Beale may
actually go on the air this evening.

554
00:32:29,072 --> 00:32:30,990
As far as I know,
Howard's going to do it.

555
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,369
You going to sit still for this, Ed?

556
00:32:35,537 --> 00:32:38,998
Yes. I think Hackett's
overstepped himself.

557
00:32:39,166 --> 00:32:41,792
There's some kind of corporate
maneuvering going on, Max.

558
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:44,170
Hackett is clearly
forcing a confrontation.

559
00:32:44,338 --> 00:32:47,548
That would account for his behavior
at the stockholders' meeting.

560
00:32:47,716 --> 00:32:51,302
However, I think he's making a serious
mistake with this Beale business.

561
00:32:51,928 --> 00:32:56,599
I suspect CCA will be upset
at Hackett's presumptuousness.

562
00:32:56,767 --> 00:32:58,851
Certainly Mr. Jensen will.

563
00:32:59,019 --> 00:33:02,063
So I'm going to let Hackett
have his head for a while.

564
00:33:02,606 --> 00:33:05,149
He just might lose it
over this Beale business.

565
00:33:09,488 --> 00:33:12,156
I'd like you to reconsider
your resignation, Max.

566
00:33:12,699 --> 00:33:14,950
I assume that Hackett
wouldn't take such steps...

567
00:33:15,118 --> 00:33:17,119
...without some support
on the CCA board.

568
00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:20,081
I'll have to go directly to Mr. Jensen.

569
00:33:20,248 --> 00:33:23,250
When that happens, I'm going
to need every friend I've got.

570
00:33:23,418 --> 00:33:27,088
And I certainly don't want Hackett's
people in all of the divisional positions.

571
00:33:27,255 --> 00:33:29,382
So I'd like you to stay on, Max.

572
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:35,346
Of course, Ed.

573
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:38,933
Thank you, Max.

574
00:33:39,976 --> 00:33:44,271
This has been the UBS evening
news with Howard Beale.

575
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:49,527
The initial response to the new
Howard Beale Show was not auspicatory.

576
00:33:49,695 --> 00:33:53,948
The press was without exception hostile
and the industry reaction negative.

577
00:33:54,116 --> 00:33:57,118
The ratings for the Thursday
and Friday shows were both 14.

578
00:33:57,285 --> 00:33:59,245
But Monday's rating dropped a point...

579
00:33:59,413 --> 00:34:02,832
...clearly suggesting the
novelty was wearing off.

580
00:34:04,292 --> 00:34:06,502
Did you know there are
a number of psychics...

581
00:34:06,670 --> 00:34:09,296
...working as licensed
brokers on Wall Street?

582
00:34:09,464 --> 00:34:12,133
Some of them counsel their
clients by use of tarot cards.

583
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:15,678
They're all pretty successful, even
in a bear market and selling short.

584
00:34:15,846 --> 00:34:19,265
I met one of them last week and
thought of doing a show around her.

585
00:34:19,433 --> 00:34:22,101
The Wayward Witch of Wall
Street, something like that.

586
00:34:22,269 --> 00:34:24,770
If her tips were any good,
she could wreck the market.

587
00:34:24,938 --> 00:34:30,317
So I called her this morning and asked
her how she was on predicting the future.

588
00:34:30,485 --> 00:34:33,028
She said she was occasionally prescient.

589
00:34:33,196 --> 00:34:35,072
For example, she said:

590
00:34:35,240 --> 00:34:37,825
"I just had a fleeting vision of you...

591
00:34:37,993 --> 00:34:40,870
...sitting in an office with
a craggy middle-aged man...

592
00:34:41,037 --> 00:34:44,582
...with whom you are, or will
be, emotionally involved. "

593
00:34:44,750 --> 00:34:46,000
And here I am.

594
00:34:48,462 --> 00:34:50,337
And she does all this with tarot cards?

595
00:34:50,505 --> 00:34:53,966
No. This one operates on parapsychology.

596
00:34:54,134 --> 00:34:58,345
She has trance-like episodes and
feels things in her energy field.

597
00:34:59,473 --> 00:35:01,974
I think this lady could
be very useful to you, Max.

598
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:04,018
- In what way?
- Well...

599
00:35:04,186 --> 00:35:07,354
...you put on a news show and
here's somebody who can predict...

600
00:35:07,522 --> 00:35:09,106
...tomorrow's news for you.

601
00:35:09,274 --> 00:35:11,901
Her name, aptly enough, is Sibyl.

602
00:35:12,068 --> 00:35:13,402
Sibyl the Soothsayer.

603
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:17,156
You could give her two minutes of trance
at the end of a Howard Beale Show...

604
00:35:17,324 --> 00:35:18,699
...say, once a week, Friday...

605
00:35:18,867 --> 00:35:21,952
...which is suggestively
occult, and she could oraculate.

606
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:26,165
Then next week everyone tunes in to
see how good her predictions were.

607
00:35:27,042 --> 00:35:28,584
Maybe she could do the weather.

608
00:35:30,712 --> 00:35:33,923
Your Network News is going to need
some help, Max, if it's gonna hold.

609
00:35:34,090 --> 00:35:36,383
Beale doesn't do the
angry-man thing well at all.

610
00:35:36,551 --> 00:35:40,221
He's too, uh, kvetchy. He's being irascible.
We want a prophet, not a curmudgeon.

611
00:35:40,388 --> 00:35:42,014
He should do more apocalyptic doom.

612
00:35:42,182 --> 00:35:46,560
I think you should take on a couple of
writers to write some jeremiads for him.

613
00:35:47,062 --> 00:35:49,063
I see you don't fancy my suggestions.

614
00:35:51,608 --> 00:35:53,317
Hell, you're not serious, are you?

615
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:56,028
Oh, I'm serious.

616
00:35:57,030 --> 00:36:00,866
The fact is I could make your Beale
Show the highest-rated news show...

617
00:36:01,034 --> 00:36:04,370
...in television, if you'd
let me have a crack at it.

618
00:36:04,621 --> 00:36:09,750
- What do you mean, "have a crack at it"?
- I'd like to program it for you. Develop it.

619
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:14,797
I wouldn't interfere with the actual
news itself, but TV is showbiz, Max.

620
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:18,592
And even the news has to
have a little showmanship.

621
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:21,136
My God, you are serious.

622
00:36:21,304 --> 00:36:25,099
Oh. I watched your 6:00 news
today. It's straight tabloid.

623
00:36:25,267 --> 00:36:28,811
You had a minute and a half of that
lady riding a bike naked in Central Park.

624
00:36:28,979 --> 00:36:32,147
You had less than a minute of hard
national and international news.

625
00:36:32,315 --> 00:36:34,900
It was all sex, scandal,
brutal crimes, sports...

626
00:36:35,443 --> 00:36:38,112
...children with incurable
diseases and lost puppies.

627
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:42,032
I don't think I'll listen to any protestations
of high standards of journalism...

628
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,785
...when you're soliciting
audiences like the rest of us.

629
00:36:44,953 --> 00:36:48,455
All I'm saying is, if you're
gonna hustle, at least do it right.

630
00:36:48,623 --> 00:36:50,791
I'm gonna bring this up
at tomorrow's meeting.

631
00:36:50,959 --> 00:36:54,336
I don't like network hassles. I was
hoping you and I could work this out.

632
00:36:54,504 --> 00:36:56,171
Now that's why I'm here.

633
00:36:57,048 --> 00:37:00,426
And I was hoping that you were
looking for an emotional involvement...

634
00:37:00,594 --> 00:37:02,595
...with a craggy middle-aged man.

635
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:06,181
Oh, I wouldn't rule that out entirely.

636
00:37:09,519 --> 00:37:11,687
All right, Diana.

637
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:14,356
You bring up all your ideas
at the meeting tomorrow...

638
00:37:14,524 --> 00:37:16,483
...because if you don't, I will.

639
00:37:17,193 --> 00:37:19,820
I think Howard's making a
goddamn fool of himself...

640
00:37:19,988 --> 00:37:23,657
...and so does everybody that
Howard and I know in this industry.

641
00:37:24,117 --> 00:37:27,161
It was a fluke. It didn't work.

642
00:37:27,621 --> 00:37:31,415
So tomorrow, Howard goes
back to the old format...

643
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:34,627
...and all of this gutter
depravity comes to an end.

644
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:38,964
Okay.

645
00:37:46,431 --> 00:37:48,557
I don't get it, Diana.

646
00:37:49,517 --> 00:37:53,020
You hung around until 7:30 and
then came all the way down here...

647
00:37:53,188 --> 00:37:55,689
...just to pitch a couple
of loony showbiz ideas...

648
00:37:55,857 --> 00:37:59,443
...when you knew goddamn well I'd
laugh you right out of the office.

649
00:37:59,611 --> 00:38:01,487
I don't get it.

650
00:38:02,155 --> 00:38:04,156
What's your scam in this?

651
00:38:04,324 --> 00:38:06,867
Max, my little visit here tonight...

652
00:38:07,035 --> 00:38:11,288
...was a gesture made out of
your stature in the industry...

653
00:38:11,665 --> 00:38:15,376
...and because I personally admired you
since I was a kid majoring in speech...

654
00:38:15,543 --> 00:38:17,086
...at the University of Missouri.

655
00:38:18,338 --> 00:38:20,172
Sooner or later, with or without you...

656
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:22,675
...I'm going to take over
your Network News show...

657
00:38:22,842 --> 00:38:25,094
...and I figured I might
as well start tonight.

658
00:38:25,261 --> 00:38:28,389
I, uh, think I once gave a lecture...

659
00:38:28,556 --> 00:38:31,976
...at the University of Missouri.

660
00:38:32,143 --> 00:38:33,394
I was in the audience.

661
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:37,606
I had a terrible schoolgirl crush
on you for a couple of months.

662
00:38:38,483 --> 00:38:40,943
If we could get back for
a moment to that gypsy...

663
00:38:41,111 --> 00:38:46,782
...who predicted all that about, uh,
emotional involvements and middle-aged men.

664
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:49,576
What are you doing for dinner tonight?

665
00:38:59,129 --> 00:39:02,089
I can't make it tonight,
love. Call me tomorrow.

666
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:07,678
- Do you have a favorite restaurant?
- I eat anything.

667
00:39:08,722 --> 00:39:10,848
Son of a bitch, I get a
feeling I'm being made.

668
00:39:11,016 --> 00:39:12,558
You are.

669
00:39:13,268 --> 00:39:16,729
Ah, I've got to warn you, I don't
do anything on my first date.

670
00:39:16,896 --> 00:39:18,605
We'll see.

671
00:39:24,237 --> 00:39:26,780
Schmuck, what are you getting into?

672
00:39:48,053 --> 00:39:52,097
I was married for four years
and pretended to be happy...

673
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:55,601
...and had six years of analysis
and pretended to be sane.

674
00:39:56,478 --> 00:39:59,188
My husband ran off with his boyfriend...

675
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:01,231
...and I had an affair with my analyst.

676
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:04,610
He told me I was the
worst lay he'd ever had.

677
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:08,906
I can't tell you how many men
have told me what a lousy lay I am.

678
00:40:09,074 --> 00:40:11,408
I apparently have a
masculine temperament.

679
00:40:11,993 --> 00:40:15,329
I arouse quickly,
consummate prematurely...

680
00:40:15,497 --> 00:40:19,166
...and can't wait to get my clothes
back on and get out of that bedroom.

681
00:40:19,709 --> 00:40:24,379
I seem to be inept at
everything except my work.

682
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:29,343
I'm good at my work. So
I confine myself to that.

683
00:40:29,636 --> 00:40:32,971
All I want out of life is
a 30 share and a 20 rating.

684
00:40:34,724 --> 00:40:36,642
You're married, surely?

685
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:40,145
Twenty-five years.

686
00:40:40,855 --> 00:40:44,024
I have a married daughter in
Seattle who's six months pregnant...

687
00:40:44,776 --> 00:40:49,988
...a younger girl who's starting
at Northwestern in January.

688
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:54,243
Well, Max, here we are.

689
00:40:56,204 --> 00:40:58,872
Middle-aged man reaffirming
his middle-aged manhood...

690
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:02,084
...and a terrified young
woman with a father complex.

691
00:41:02,252 --> 00:41:05,212
What sort of script do you
