1365
01:28:46,279 --> 01:28:49,240
...and they hold every pledge we've got.

1366
01:28:50,492 --> 01:28:53,244
We need that Saudi money bad.

1367
01:28:55,414 --> 01:28:58,332
Disaster. The show is a disaster.

1368
01:28:59,751 --> 01:29:02,920
Unmitigated disaster. The death knell.

1369
01:29:04,423 --> 01:29:08,259
I'm ruined. I'm dead. Finished.

1370
01:29:08,927 --> 01:29:12,847
Maybe we're overstating
Beale's clout with the public.

1371
01:29:14,016 --> 01:29:16,600
An hour ago, Clarence McElheny
called me from New York.

1372
01:29:16,768 --> 01:29:19,979
It was 10:00 in the east and our
people in the White House report...

1373
01:29:20,147 --> 01:29:22,982
...they were already
knee-deep in telegrams.

1374
01:29:23,150 --> 01:29:28,029
By tomorrow morning, they'll
be suffocating in telegrams.

1375
01:29:28,196 --> 01:29:30,823
- Can the government stop the deal?
- They can hold it up.

1376
01:29:30,991 --> 01:29:34,410
The SEC could hold this deal up
for 20 years, if they wanted to.

1377
01:29:34,661 --> 01:29:36,037
I'm finished.

1378
01:29:36,204 --> 01:29:39,707
Any second that phone's gonna ring and
Clarence McElheny is gonna tell me...

1379
01:29:39,875 --> 01:29:42,710
...Mr. Jensen wants me in
his office tomorrow morning...

1380
01:29:42,878 --> 01:29:46,338
...so he can personally
chop my head off.

1381
01:29:47,007 --> 01:29:49,383
Four hours ago, I was
the sun god at CCA.

1382
01:29:49,551 --> 01:29:53,637
Mr. Jensen's hand-picked
golden boy, the heir apparent.

1383
01:29:53,805 --> 01:29:58,392
Now, ha, ha, I'm a man
without a corporation.

1384
01:29:59,478 --> 01:30:01,645
Let's get back to Howard Beale.

1385
01:30:02,981 --> 01:30:06,150
You're not seriously gonna
pull Beale off the air?

1386
01:30:10,447 --> 01:30:14,450
Mr. Jensen's unhappy with Howard
Beale and wants him discontinued.

1387
01:30:14,618 --> 01:30:16,994
But he may be unhappy, but
he isn't stupid enough...

1388
01:30:17,162 --> 01:30:20,039
...to withdraw the number-one
show on television out of pique.

1389
01:30:20,207 --> 01:30:23,084
Two billion dollars isn't
pique! That's the wrath of God!

1390
01:30:23,251 --> 01:30:25,586
And the wrath of God
wants Howard Beale fired!

1391
01:30:25,754 --> 01:30:28,255
Every other network will
grab him the minute he walks.

1392
01:30:28,423 --> 01:30:31,133
He'll be back on the air for
ABC and we'll lose 20 points...

1393
01:30:31,301 --> 01:30:33,844
I'm gonna impale the son of
a bitch with a sharp stick!

1394
01:30:34,012 --> 01:30:36,680
Forty million loss in revenues.
- I'll take out a contract.

1395
01:30:36,848 --> 01:30:40,142
- Let's not discount federal action...
- I'll hire professional killers.

1396
01:30:40,310 --> 01:30:45,481
No, I'll do it myself. I'll
strangle him with a sash cord!

1397
01:30:45,816 --> 01:30:48,984
...and a breach of the consent decree.
I don't think Jensen's gonna fire anybody.

1398
01:30:54,783 --> 01:30:56,200
Hackett.

1399
01:30:58,411 --> 01:31:01,872
Yes, Clarence. I've
already booked my flight.

1400
01:31:03,583 --> 01:31:05,918
Uh, well, can you give me a
little more time than that?

1401
01:31:06,086 --> 01:31:08,796
I've got the red-eye flight,
I won't be back in New York...

1402
01:31:08,964 --> 01:31:11,132
...till 6 tomorrow morning.

1403
01:31:13,093 --> 01:31:15,136
That'll be just fine.

1404
01:31:15,387 --> 01:31:17,054
I'll see you then.

1405
01:31:25,689 --> 01:31:28,983
Mr. Jensen wants to meet
Howard Beale personally.

1406
01:31:29,526 --> 01:31:33,279
He wants Mr. Beale in his
office at 10:00 tomorrow morning.

1407
01:31:39,786 --> 01:31:42,496
The final revelation is at hand.

1408
01:31:42,664 --> 01:31:46,750
I have seen the shattering
fulgurations of ultimate clarity.

1409
01:31:46,918 --> 01:31:51,755
The light is impending. I
bear witness to the light!

1410
01:32:12,569 --> 01:32:14,153
Good morning, Mr. Beale.

1411
01:32:14,321 --> 01:32:17,031
- They tell me you're a madman.
- Only desultorily.

1412
01:32:17,199 --> 01:32:19,533
- How are you now?
- I'm as mad as a hatter.

1413
01:32:19,701 --> 01:32:21,368
Who isn't?

1414
01:32:21,953 --> 01:32:24,121
I'm going to take you
into our conference room.

1415
01:32:24,289 --> 01:32:27,625
Seems more seemly a setting
for what I have to say to you.

1416
01:32:28,960 --> 01:32:31,378
I started as a salesman, Mr. Beale.

1417
01:32:31,546 --> 01:32:34,423
I sold sewing machines
and automobile parts...

1418
01:32:34,591 --> 01:32:37,509
...hairbrushes and electronic equipment.

1419
01:32:37,677 --> 01:32:40,012
They say I can sell anything.

1420
01:32:40,847 --> 01:32:44,099
I'd like to try to
sell something to you.

1421
01:32:47,687 --> 01:32:51,315
Valhalla, Mr. Beale. Please, sit down.

1422
01:33:20,804 --> 01:33:25,599
You have meddled with the primal
forces of nature, Mr. Beale.

1423
01:33:25,767 --> 01:33:30,104
And I won't have it! Is that clear?

1424
01:33:30,397 --> 01:33:32,856
You think you've merely
stopped a business deal.

1425
01:33:33,024 --> 01:33:34,566
That is not the case.

1426
01:33:34,734 --> 01:33:37,653
The Arabs have taken billions
of dollars out of this country...

1427
01:33:37,821 --> 01:33:39,697
...and now they must put it back!

1428
01:33:39,864 --> 01:33:45,035
It is ebb and flow, tidal
gravity, it is ecological balance.

1429
01:33:46,621 --> 01:33:48,372
You are an old man...

1430
01:33:48,540 --> 01:33:52,376
...who thinks in terms
of nations and peoples.

1431
01:33:52,544 --> 01:33:55,921
There are no nations, there are
no peoples. There are no Russians.

1432
01:33:56,089 --> 01:33:58,549
There are no Arabs.
There are no Third Worlds.

1433
01:33:58,717 --> 01:33:59,883
There is no West!

1434
01:34:00,051 --> 01:34:05,014
There is only one
holistic system of systems.

1435
01:34:05,181 --> 01:34:07,391
One vast and immane...

1436
01:34:07,559 --> 01:34:10,394
...interwoven, interacting,
multi-variate...

1437
01:34:10,562 --> 01:34:13,731
...multinational dominion of dollars.

1438
01:34:13,898 --> 01:34:17,026
Petrol dollars,
electro-dollars, multi-dollars.

1439
01:34:17,193 --> 01:34:22,948
Reichsmarks, rins,
rubles, pounds and shekels.

1440
01:34:24,284 --> 01:34:28,746
It is the international system
of currency which determines...

1441
01:34:28,913 --> 01:34:32,291
...the totality of life on this planet.

1442
01:34:33,251 --> 01:34:37,755
That is the natural
order of things today.

1443
01:34:38,882 --> 01:34:42,634
That is the atomic...

1444
01:34:42,802 --> 01:34:44,928
...and subatomic...

1445
01:34:45,096 --> 01:34:50,434
...and galactic
structure of things today.

1446
01:34:51,186 --> 01:34:53,270
And you have meddled...

1447
01:34:53,438 --> 01:34:57,983
...with the primal forces of nature!

1448
01:34:58,276 --> 01:35:03,781
And you will atone.

1449
01:35:04,407 --> 01:35:06,784
Am I getting it through
to you, Mr. Beale?

1450
01:35:10,246 --> 01:35:14,792
You get up on your
little 21-inch screen...

1451
01:35:15,502 --> 01:35:20,381
...and howl about America and democracy.

1452
01:35:20,965 --> 01:35:25,302
There is no America.
There is no democracy.

1453
01:35:25,470 --> 01:35:30,974
There is only IBM and ITT and AT&T...

1454
01:35:31,142 --> 01:35:36,730
...and Dupont, Dow,
Union Carbide, and Exxon.

1455
01:35:36,898 --> 01:35:40,484
Those are the nations
of the world today.

1456
01:35:40,860 --> 01:35:44,988
What do you think the Russians talk about
in their councils of state? Karl Marx?

1457
01:35:45,156 --> 01:35:47,491
They get out their linear
programming charts...

1458
01:35:47,659 --> 01:35:50,160
...statistical decision
theories, minimax solutions...

1459
01:35:50,328 --> 01:35:53,789
...and compute price-cost probabilities
of transactions and investments...

1460
01:35:53,957 --> 01:35:54,998
...just like we do.

1461
01:35:55,500 --> 01:35:59,753
We no longer live in a world of
nations and ideologies, Mr. Beale.

1462
01:35:59,921 --> 01:36:04,591
The world is a college
of corporations...

1463
01:36:05,260 --> 01:36:12,141
...inexorably determined by the
immutable bylaws of business.

1464
01:36:14,227 --> 01:36:17,187
The world is a business, Mr. Beale.

1465
01:36:19,107 --> 01:36:23,068
It has been since man
crawled out of the slime.

1466
01:36:25,864 --> 01:36:30,784
And our children will live, Mr. Beale...

1467
01:36:32,162 --> 01:36:33,745
...to see that...

1468
01:36:36,040 --> 01:36:38,792
...perfect world...

1469
01:36:39,794 --> 01:36:43,005
...in which there's no war or famine...

1470
01:36:43,173 --> 01:36:46,508
...oppression or brutality.

1471
01:36:47,552 --> 01:36:51,513
One vast and ecumenical
holding company...

1472
01:36:51,681 --> 01:36:55,976
...for whom all men will work
to serve a common profit...

1473
01:36:56,144 --> 01:37:00,397
...in which all men will
hold a share of stock...

1474
01:37:01,649 --> 01:37:04,568
...all necessities provided...

1475
01:37:05,278 --> 01:37:09,114
...all anxieties tranquillized...

1476
01:37:10,074 --> 01:37:13,994
...all boredom amused.

1477
01:37:19,959 --> 01:37:24,546
And I have chosen you, Mr. Beale...

1478
01:37:24,714 --> 01:37:27,216
...to preach this evangel.

1479
01:37:27,884 --> 01:37:29,510
Why me?

1480
01:37:30,762 --> 01:37:33,597
Because you're on television, dummy.

1481
01:37:34,474 --> 01:37:39,937
Sixty million people watch you every
night of the week, Monday through Friday.

1482
01:37:40,813 --> 01:37:43,106
I have seen the face of God.

1483
01:37:45,652 --> 01:37:48,237
You just might be right, Mr. Beale.

1484
01:37:49,781 --> 01:37:52,115
That evening, Howard
Beale went on the air...

1485
01:37:52,283 --> 01:37:54,952
...to preach the corporate
cosmology of Arthur Jensen.

1486
01:37:55,119 --> 01:37:57,996
Last night I got up here
and asked you people...

1487
01:37:58,164 --> 01:38:02,459
...to stand up and fight for your
heritage, and you did, and it was beautiful.

1488
01:38:02,627 --> 01:38:05,629
Six million telegrams were
received at the White House.

1489
01:38:05,797 --> 01:38:08,966
The Arab takeover of
CCA has been stopped.

1490
01:38:09,133 --> 01:38:14,805
The people spoke, the people won. It
was a radiant eruption of democracy.

1491
01:38:14,973 --> 01:38:19,017
But I think that was it, fellas.

1492
01:38:19,185 --> 01:38:21,895
That sort of thing is not
likely to happen again.

1493
01:38:22,105 --> 01:38:25,065
Because at the bottom of
all our terrified souls...

1494
01:38:25,233 --> 01:38:28,277
...we know that democracy
is a dying giant...

1495
01:38:28,444 --> 01:38:33,240
...a sick, sick, dying, decaying, political
concept writhing in its final pain.

1496
01:38:33,408 --> 01:38:36,994
I don't mean that the United
States is finished as a world power.

1497
01:38:37,161 --> 01:38:39,329
The States is the richest
and most powerful...

1498
01:38:39,497 --> 01:38:42,457
...the most advanced country,
light years ahead of any country.

1499
01:38:42,625 --> 01:38:45,335
I don't mean the communists
are gonna take over the world.

1500
01:38:45,503 --> 01:38:48,839
The communists are deader than
we are. What is finished...

1501
01:38:50,466 --> 01:38:53,927
...is the idea that this great
country is dedicated to the freedom...

1502
01:38:54,095 --> 01:38:57,806
...and flourishing of
every individual in it.

1503
01:38:58,891 --> 01:39:01,852
It's the individual that's finished.

1504
01:39:02,270 --> 01:39:06,189
It's the single, solitary,
human being that's finished.

1505
01:39:07,066 --> 01:39:11,111
It's every single one of you
out there that's finished.

1506
01:39:11,654 --> 01:39:13,864
Because this is no longer...

1507
01:39:14,032 --> 01:39:17,743
...a nation of independent individuals.

1508
01:39:18,036 --> 01:39:20,829
It's a nation of some
200-odd million...

1509
01:39:20,997 --> 01:39:23,540
...transistorized, deodorized...

1510
01:39:23,708 --> 01:39:29,212
...whiter than white steel-belted bodies,
totally unnecessary as human beings...

1511
01:39:29,380 --> 01:39:32,758
...and as replaceable as piston rods.

1512
01:39:43,394 --> 01:39:46,605
Well, the time has come to say...

1513
01:39:46,773 --> 01:39:49,941
...is "dehumanization" such a bad word?

1514
01:39:50,318 --> 01:39:53,403
Whether it's good or
bad, that's what is so.

1515
01:39:53,571 --> 01:39:58,742
The whole world is becoming humanoid,
creatures that look human but aren't.

1516
01:39:59,202 --> 01:40:00,577
The whole world, not just us.

1517
01:40:00,745 --> 01:40:04,915
We're just the most advanced
country, so we're getting there first.

1518
01:40:05,583 --> 01:40:10,545
The whole world's people are
becoming mass-produced, programmed...

1519
01:40:10,713 --> 01:40:12,464
...numbered insensate things.

1520
01:40:12,882 --> 01:40:14,925
It was a perfectly
admissible argument...

1521
01:40:15,093 --> 01:40:17,678
...that Howard Beale advanced
in the days that followed.

1522
01:40:17,845 --> 01:40:20,722
It was, however, also
a very depressing one.

1523
01:40:20,890 --> 01:40:24,226
Nobody particularly cared to hear
his life was utterly valueless.

1524
01:40:24,394 --> 01:40:26,228
By the end of the first week in June...

1525
01:40:26,396 --> 01:40:29,147
...the Howard Beale Show dropped
one point in the ratings...

1526
01:40:29,315 --> 01:40:33,944
...and its trend of shares dipped under
48 for the first time since last November.

1527
01:40:34,112 --> 01:40:38,115
You're his goddamn agent. I'm counting on
you to talk some sense into the lunatic.

1528
01:40:38,282 --> 01:40:41,785
Nobody wants to hear about dying
democracy and dehumanization.

1529
01:40:42,412 --> 01:40:43,495
I'm sorry I'm late.

1530
01:40:43,663 --> 01:40:45,872
We're starting to get
rumbles from the agencies.

1531
01:40:46,040 --> 01:40:48,834
Another couple of weeks and the
sponsors will be bailing out!

1532
01:40:49,001 --> 01:40:52,129
This is a breach of contract. This
isn't the Howard Beale we signed.

1533
01:40:52,296 --> 01:40:56,591
Get him off that corporate universe kick,
or so help me, I'll pull it off the air!

1534
01:40:56,759 --> 01:40:59,886
I told him, Lou! I've been
telling him every day for a week!

1535
01:41:00,054 --> 01:41:03,140
I'm sick of telling
him. Now you tell him!

1536
01:41:11,023 --> 01:41:12,399
Jesus Christ.

1537
01:41:15,903 --> 01:41:18,238
You could help me out with
Howard if you wanted to.

1538
01:41:18,406 --> 01:41:20,657
He listens to you.
You're his best friend.

1539
01:41:20,825 --> 01:41:23,285
I'm tired of all this
hysteria about Howard Beale.

1540
01:41:23,453 --> 01:41:26,121
Every time you come from seeing
somebody in your family...

1541
01:41:26,289 --> 01:41:28,623
...you come back in one
of these middle-aged moods.

1542
01:41:28,791 --> 01:41:31,835
I'm tired of finding you on the
telephone every time I turn around.

1543
01:41:32,003 --> 01:41:34,838
I'm tired of being an
accessory in your life.

1544
01:41:35,298 --> 01:41:37,841
And I'm tired of pretending
to write this dumb book...

1545
01:41:38,009 --> 01:41:41,178
...about my maverick days in the
great early years of television.

1546
01:41:41,345 --> 01:41:45,015
Every goddamned executive fired from
a network in the last 20 years...

1547
01:41:45,183 --> 01:41:49,186
...has written this dumb book about
the great early years of television.

1548
01:41:49,353 --> 01:41:52,647
And nobody wants a dumb,
damn, goddamn book...

1549
01:41:52,815 --> 01:41:55,025
...about the early days of television.

1550
01:41:55,193 --> 01:41:58,236
Terrific, Max! Maybe you can start
a whole new career as an actor.

1551
01:41:58,404 --> 01:42:00,113
It's the truth.

1552
01:42:00,865 --> 01:42:05,619
After living with you for six months,
I'm turning into one of your scripts.

1553
01:42:06,412 --> 01:42:08,872
Well, this is not a script, Diana.

1554
01:42:09,207 --> 01:42:12,834
There's some real,
actual life going on here.

1555
01:42:13,628 --> 01:42:17,214
I went to visit my wife today because
she's in a state of depression...

1556
01:42:17,423 --> 01:42:21,051
...so depressed that my daughter flew
all the way from Seattle to be with her.

1557
01:42:21,219 --> 01:42:23,220
And I feel lousy about that.

1558
01:42:23,387 --> 01:42:27,516
I feel lousy about the pain that
I've caused my wife and my kids.

1559
01:42:27,683 --> 01:42:29,601
I feel guilty and
conscience-stricken...

1560
01:42:29,769 --> 01:42:32,395
...and all of those things
that you think sentimental...

1561
01:42:32,563 --> 01:42:36,525
...but which my generation
calls simple, human decency.

1562
01:42:40,530 --> 01:42:42,572
And I miss my home...

1563
01:42:43,282 --> 01:42:46,117
...because I'm beginning
to get scared shitless.

1564
01:42:46,285 --> 01:42:49,746
Because all of a sudden it's closer
to the end than it is to the beginning.

1565
01:42:49,914 --> 01:42:52,874
And death is suddenly a
perceptible thing to me...

1566
01:42:53,042 --> 01:42:55,544
...with definable features.

1567
01:42:59,590 --> 01:43:03,969
You're dealing with a man that
has primal doubts, Diana...

1568
01:43:04,303 --> 01:43:06,763
...and you've got to cope with it.

1569
01:43:07,348 --> 01:43:11,434
I'm not some guy discussing male
menopause on the Barbara Walters Show.

1570
01:43:12,103 --> 01:43:15,438
I'm the man that you presumably love.

1571
01:43:16,524 --> 01:43:19,442
I'm part of your life.

1572
01:43:19,610 --> 01:43:23,280
I live here. I'm real.

1573
01:43:24,448 --> 01:43:27,325
You can't switch to another station.

1574
01:43:34,792 --> 01:43:37,627
What exactly is it you want me to do?

1575
01:43:41,632 --> 01:43:44,676
I just want you to love me.

1576
01:43:45,928 --> 01:43:49,389
I just want you to love
me, primal doubts and all.

1577
01:43:51,726 --> 01:43:54,144
You understand that, don't you?

1578
01:43:59,150 --> 01:44:01,443
I don't know how to do that.

1579
01:44:13,164 --> 01:44:15,790
I'll be with you in a minute, Max.

1580
01:44:20,922 --> 01:44:22,422
By the first week in July...

1581
01:44:22,590 --> 01:44:24,716
...the Howard Beale
Show was down 11 points.

1582
01:44:24,884 --> 01:44:26,718
Hysteria swept through the network.

1583
01:44:26,886 --> 01:44:28,553
He's a plague. He's smallpox.

1584
01:44:28,721 --> 01:44:31,222
He's typhoid. I don't wanna
follow his goddamn show.

1585
01:44:31,390 --> 01:44:32,724
I want out of that 8:00 spot.

1586
01:44:32,892 --> 01:44:35,602
I've got enough troubles without
Howard Beale as a lead-in!

1587
01:44:35,770 --> 01:44:37,854
Scheduled me against
Tony Orlando and Dawn.

1588
01:44:38,022 --> 01:44:41,274
NBC's got Little House on the
Prairie. ABC's got The Bionic Woman.

1589
01:44:41,442 --> 01:44:44,027
Do something! You gotta do
something about Howard Beale!

1590
01:44:44,195 --> 01:44:46,363
Get him off the air! Get him off!

